      <accessrestrict id="aspace_arest">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The Papers are open to researchers by appointment. There are no restricted materials in the collection. Please contact the Special Collections staff to schedule an appointment.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_d1e214">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The New Haven Music Club Papers were established in the Music Library of Yale University by Mrs. Louis Hemingway, Jr., a former Club member.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <userestrict id="aspace_urest">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>The New Haven Music Club Papers are the physical property of the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University. Copyrights belong to the composers and authors, or their legal heirs and assigns.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_cite">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>MSS 4, The New Haven Music Club Papers in the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_arr1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged chronologically.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The New Haven Music Club Papers consist of 3 ledger books in which are entered membership lists, programs, financial records, and photographs documenting 25 years of the Club's history.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_bh1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Music Club, a local women's club, was created in 1913 in New Haven, Conn. Meetings included concerts and recitals presented once every month by Club members. The membership of the Club consisted of Yale faculty wives and women from the New Haven community. The Music Club's last meeting was held in March, 1946.</p>  
      </bioghist>
